        <updateDate>2003-09-12T18:02:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>First Responders Enhancement Act - Amends the Omnibus Crime Control and Safe Streets Act of 1968 to make certain matching fund requirements and the maximum grant limit inapplicable to a COPS (public safety and community policing; &quot;cops on the beat&quot;) grant awarded in FY 2004 or 2005. Limits funding for hiring or rehiring a career law enforcement officer to $150,000 (currently, $75,000) in the absence of a waiver by the Attorney General. Repeals a requirement that the grant application specify plans for the assumption by the applicant of a progressively larger share of the cost over time.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>First Responders Enhancement Act</title>
